# Enforce LF line endings on checkout across all platforms.
#
# Without this, Windows checkout with `core.autocrlf=true` rewrites
# every text file from LF (the form in git's object store) to CRLF
# (on the working tree). Prettier's default `endOfLine: "lf"` then
# flags every file as a formatting error and the husky pre-commit
# `format:check` hook blocks every commit — even though CI on Linux
# (LF native) passes cleanly. The divergence cost contributors
# `--no-verify` workarounds for problems that don't exist in the
# canonical form.
#
# `* text=auto` lets git detect text vs binary; `eol=lf` then forces
# LF on checkout for everything classified as text. Binary files
# (images, fonts) are detected and left alone.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-braces: explicitly mark the common binaries we ship so
# they're never accidentally converted, even if auto-detection
# guesses wrong.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.pdf binary
